# Development workflow

## Planning → implementation split

Plans are written by **Claude Code** (the CLI) and implemented by **Cursor Composer**.

- Plans live in `~/.claude/plans/` as Markdown files.
- When a plan file is shared with Composer, implement every item in the **Files Changed** table, in order.
- Do not deviate from the plan unless a step is impossible as written — in that case, implement the closest correct equivalent and note the delta.

## Handoff checklist

Before implementing a plan, run any `pnpm add <pkg>` steps listed under **Install** in a terminal first. Composer cannot install packages; it will see missing-module TypeScript errors if the package is absent.

## Keeping plans honest

If you complete an implementation that satisfies a plan, check off the matching `- [ ]` item in `README.md` roadmap in the same commit (see `maintenance.mdc`).
